Florida was awesome. Hurricane Alberto came and went, and didn't do much. My room was absolutley hilarious: Shara McClanahan, Katie Kenealy, and Katie Trautman , Sarah Fitzgerald and Me. We had the best time.  The beach was gorgeous, but I was scared of being eaten by a giant shark.  I think that one of the reasons that I loved this trip was being one of the oldest ones, and all of the older people on the trip were girls.  It was a great girl bonding trip and Im excited to get back and keep up the friendships we had all gotten to busy for.  Also I would like to say  that Brad Reekers can rap the whole baby got back song really fast. And that Dane is a horrible go fish player. (because he beat me like a bajillion times) 
        I am re-energized about what I am supposed to do with my life. I had let that fade away, and now I feel ready to do it.  I also realized that I have been asking people around me to change when I have done nothing to change myself to fit who I am and who I am becoming. That is not fair and now that I realize it, hopefully it wlil make things easier.  
                                   Speaking of sharks, I thought I saw one and freaked out, then It was only a piece of seaweed.    story of my life.
